      "writtenOn": "2026-06-02T15:40:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "cue/load doesn\u0027t quite seem like the right place for replacingRegistry.\nI\u0027m not quite sure where it should live though. mod/modregistry seems a bit\ntoo low level: although it knows about module files, it doesn\u0027t seem like it\nshould be implementing the replacement strategy.\n\nIn general, calling this thing a \"registry\" doesn\u0027t seem right, as a registry implies a straightforward\nvalue store without associated logic.\n\nMaybe the right abstraction is something like a MainModule which is instantiated\nwith an underlying registry and a module file, and can be used to resolve import\npaths and load modules.\n\nNot entirely sure yet of the best place for it to live though.",
      "revId": "d8501922880bfd1930b614e8048dd7c2530d8449",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
